SINGAPORE DAYBOOK: STX OSV Holdings, Mapletree, Chip Eng Seng

-- B y   J a n   D a h i n t e n   a n d   P h o e b e   S e d g m a n
-- 
2011-03-31T22:26:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/singapore-daybook-stx-osv-holdings-mapletree-chip-eng-seng.html
STX OSV Holdings Ltd., the world’s
biggest maker of oil-rig support vessels by sales, said it
obtained an environmental license to build its second shipyard
in  Brazil . Construction will begin in the second quarter.  WHAT TO WATCH:  *Chip Eng Seng said it terminated a Sept. 20 agreement with
Fujian Obon Building Materials to buy a 60% stake in the company.
*Friven & Co. said it appointed Darren Tan Poon Guan as chief
financial officer after Wee Liang Hiam resigned.
*Hotel Grand Central said its Christchurch hotel damaged in
February’s earthquake will remain closed and that most staff had
been made redundant. It said insurance cover for the building
exceeds the property’s book value.
*Low Keng Huat Singapore said 4Q net rose 27% to S$19.2m, while
sales fell 73% to S$39m.
*Mapletree Logistics Trust said it bought  Singapore ’s Jian Huang
building for S$24.5m.
*Pollux Properties said it won a contract worth S$1.8m to
deliver marble.
*Serial System Ltd. said its Serial Microelectronics unit will
sell 68% equity interest in Unitron Tech Co. for $1.9m.
*STX OSV Holdings said it received an environmental license to
build a shipyard in Brazil.  MARKETS:  S&P 500  down 0.2% to 1,325.83
Stoxx Europe 600 down 1% to 275.90
MSCI Asia Pacific up 0.7% to 135.78
Straits Times Index up 0.3% to 3,105.85  BTV:  *7:10 a.m.: YCMNet Advisors President/CIS Michael Yoshikami
*7:50 a.m.: Prospect AM Chairman Curtis Freeze
*8:10 a.m.: Lynas Corp Executive Chairman Nick Curtis
*8:40 a.m.: CIMB Islamic Bank CEO Badlisyah Abdul
*9:10 a.m.: BNP Head of China/HK Equities Erwin Sanft
*10:10 a.m.: TA Securities Economist Patricia Ling
